# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values.
# `.env.local` is gitignored — never commit your keys.
#
# Find these in your Supabase dashboard:
#   Project Settings → API
#   - "Project URL"        → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#   - "anon" / "public" key → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# Do NOT use the "service_role" key — it bypasses Row-Level Security
# and must never reach the browser.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ── Hardcover enrichment (optional) ───────────────────────────────────
# Used ONLY by the Netlify function (netlify/functions/hardcover.mts) to
# auto-fill edition format + series on ISBN lookup. This is NOT a VITE_
# variable — it must stay server-side and never reach the browser.
#   Production: add HARDCOVER_TOKEN in Netlify → Site settings →
#               Environment variables.
#   Local: only needed if you run `netlify dev`; put it in a (gitignored)
#          `.env` file. Plain `vite` won't run the function — the app just
#          falls back to Open Library, which is fine.
# Get the token from your Hardcover account's API settings page.
# HARDCOVER_TOKEN=
